CatDescriptText: Miss Shirley Edwards, business college student, Oakmont and Mr. Lois Helms, porter, Fifth Ward, were part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 17, 1962, pg. 7 with question: "What's wrong with the Republican party in Allegheny County?" Miss Shirley Edwards' answer reads: "They just don't have enough jobs.  And there are a lot of other things that are wrong with the party."  Mr. Lois Helms' answer reads: "Being registered as a Democrat, I don't think much of the Republican Party.  The Democratic Party is the party for me."
TitMainTitle: Two frames: Portrait of Shirley Edwards wearing cat eye sunglasses, standing in front of store window with ribbed metal walls; Portrait of Lois Helms wearing zippered leather jacket and hat, standing in front of street with automobiles and buildings
